  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 350°F.",
    "Brown the ground beef in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the onion and garlic to the skillet and cook until the onion is translucent.",
    "Stir in the Mexican seasoning and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the kidney beans to the skillet and stir to combine.",
    "Arrange 4-5 tacos shells in the bottom of a 9x13 inch baking dish.",
    "Spoon the beef and bean mixture over the shells.",
    "Top with shredded cheese and sour cream.",
    "If using, drizzle with crazy sauce.",
    "Bake for 20-25 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and bubbly.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!"
